      "text": "for i=2:\n    s[2] = \"p\" -> use the ASCII Value = 112\n    t[2] = \"t\" -> use the ASCII Value = 116\n\n    if(m1[112] != m2[116]){break}\n    \n    m1[112] = 2+1 = 3\n    m2[116] = 2+1 = 3\n\nm1 = [0.........97....112..............256] = {0.........2....3..............0}\nm2 = [0.............105...116...........256] = {0.............2...3...........0}",
